main event: A white or silvery parachute-shaped object, about half the size of a C-46 aircraft, was observed along with several silver objects hovering near it.
interesting points: The silver objects moved due east away from the parachute-shaped object.
The parachute-shaped object was initially at an elevation of 60-75 degrees, then moved due east and out of sight within 45-60 seconds.
Pilots of a C-47 aircraft were contacted, but they did not see the object.
Balloons were reported in the area, which may have been the cause of the sighting, though they could not be positively identified as the object sighted.
The sighting lasted for about 30 seconds.
sighted object: One parachute-shaped object and several silver objects
